From 14492413df52cbc7befe43a30cef0c0ff407c2bd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Felicitas Pojtinger <felicitas@pojtinger.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 15:01:38 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Examples: Manually add access to the host filesystem in the Flatpak manifests for caching without GNOME Builder or Foundry

Signed-off-by: Felicitas Pojtinger <felicitas@pojtinger.com>
---
diff --git a/examples/myapp-gnome-gomod/README.md b/examples/myapp-gnome-gomod/README.md
index e8e44f4ce50aa439cbba29b271232907a60536be..75cb8268e41d94bd3c4c1f06a2dc91936e506098 100644
--- a/examples/myapp-gnome-gomod/README.md
+++ b/examples/myapp-gnome-gomod/README.md
@@ -32,6 +32,6 @@ $ flatpak run --command=flatpak-builder-lint org.flatpak.Builder repo repo
 $ flatpak run page.codeberg.puregotk.MyAppGnomeGomod
 ```
 
-We're disabling the sandbox here because otherwise we can't access the `mylib-gtk-meson` directory.
+We're disabling the sandbox here because otherwise we can't access the `mylib-gtk-meson` directory and Go cache on the system.
 
 ![Screenshot of myapp-gnome-gomod showing the main application window](../../docs/screenshot-myapp-gnome-gomod.png)
diff --git a/examples/myapp-gnome-gomod/page.codeberg.puregotk.MyAppGnomeGomod.json b/examples/myapp-gnome-gomod/page.codeberg.puregotk.MyAppGnomeGomod.json
index 74a3e6400c108ca430980675123016e0bc6baa5c..2150ea4ca85f7484ab0c32037e8ee769dec9883d 100644
